  "texts": [
    "After correcting these errors, Wretblad et al. [109] find that complex prompting methods (e.g., DIN-SQL) might be less effective than simple zero-shot prompting.",
    "This research reveals the potential unreliability of table datasets such as BIRD, considering they are generated through human labeling, a process prone to introducing noise and errors.",
    "• Real-world workload Most datasets are derived from the Web or synthesized using templates.",
    "These publicly available online data are usually simple, as some of them are just tutorials for beginners.",
    "In contrast, tables in real-world scenarios are far more complex than these."
  ]
}